radiographic_examinations.findings: The thyroid is unremarkable. The airways are patent to the subsegmental level. There is bibasilar atelectasis. There is area of probable round atelectasis in the left lower lobe, but an underlying consolidation cannot be ruled out. The heart and pericardium are unremarkable. The aorta and pulmonary arteries are well opacified. There is no pulmonary embolism in the main, right, left, lobar, segmental pulmonary arteries. Though not designed for assessment of intra-abdominal organs, the liver appears fatty. The visualized portions of the spleen and stomach appear unremarkable.
